{
  "texts": [
    "The bidirectional LSTM was trained to detect and classify 40 different vulnerability types.",
    "They developed a new benchmark from SARD and NVD, featuring 116 CWE-IDs and 33,409 C/C++ programs, to evaluate 𝜇VulDeePecker.",
    "This benchmark demonstrated that 𝜇VulDeePecker significantly improves multiclass classification and detection capabilities by integrating control dependence in addition to data dependence.",
    "In summary, the reviewed studies on AI-driven vulnerability classification address various aspects of the problem but differ in their approaches and focus areas.",
    "Some research [7,47,50,119,228] concentrates on leveraging vulnerability descriptions for classification, which may not always be available in early development stages."
  ]
}